{"name":"Shall be risen","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> If you are Broken or your HP drops to -1, you come back alive with d4 HP. You cannot resuscitate again until 2d4 days have passed.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"04066799-33a3-4aee-8136-67f2fc09eb8b"}
{"name":"ICHOR OF ROT","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The foul fluids of your god's rot run from your hands-a black stigmata. As an DR12 attack you can wipe your hands on the bare skin of your assailants, who must then pass a DR12 Toughness test or descend into frothing spasms for two turns.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"04a77f26-04e3-44e1-9d0a-ef7a7f8a7d1e"}
{"name":"Ancient Gore-Hound","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Asthmatic, deluded and on its last legs, this wizened creature still has a superb nose and can sniffle up treasure in the most disgusting debris. Attacks with DR10 (bite d6). Defends with DR12, 10 HP. Becomes frenzied around goblins and berserkers.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"0e43c362-9723-44b2-bf6f-ac8d13a6501c"}
{"name":"LAUGHING HYAENIDAE","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> bite d6. Your raging sounds force a morale roll.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"147927c4-b0e0-45e8-ac5d-98717aae332d"}
{"name":"Mental Projection","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The ability to project your consciousness allowing for remote viewing or sensing.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"15b5c35b-7afb-4a6e-a45d-f8a5dce7eeca"}
{"name":"FORSAKEN HOG","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Make two attacks per round with your Bite (d4). - Thick Hide= -d4 incoming damage Slop= Incoming melee attacks are -2. Failed Morale checks cause Infection.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"164464be-9b0e-4b58-ae5e-53a3d8c4809f"}
{"name":"THE DEVIL'S AQUIFER","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The horn of a beelzebubonic creature from the deepest depths of the Endless Sea. When blown, the lungs of your enemies fill with seawater, should they fail a Toughness test against DR14; a round must be spent expelling it before doing anything else.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"18a5178f-650f-41ee-94f8-a5f1aa243883"}
{"name":"Levitation","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The ability to float or fly. Movement is the same as walking. Lose 1 HP every round you continuously levitate past the first.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"19f8ab78-4388-4116-b955-c3fe1b6e7b40"}
{"name":"Speaker of Truths","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Twice per day use your wisdom, knowledge, advice and inner calm to bring clarity to a creature of your choice. The DR of the next test they undertake is lowered by 4.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"1b5332a6-62a4-4c0d-82be-3c2541995598"}
{"name":"LORD OF NOTHING","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You wear a bizarre arrangement of garments and scraps that make you look like the parody of a king or queen. Still, you gain +2 to rolls to impress the easily fooled.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"20240c98-d0fe-4f43-acb7-ba0aa5f2068d"}
{"name":"Cursed Coin","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> An ancient gold coin taken from heretics on the isle of Cr'lut. Until you return it, you are doomed to a cursed fate</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2032cc9a-71fb-43d7-b13e-654f8e38a9da"}
{"name":"DIGITIGRADE LIMBS","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p>  You can escape any bindings, and fit through tiny spaces. Tests involving flexibility are -4 DR.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"24fb0b9f-49fb-473e-b3e8-402033363e46"}
{"name":"Covenant Of The Flesh","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Consuming your meat has healing effects. You can cut a small piece of yourself to give to someone else. You lose d2 HP and they recover d4 HP. If they had an illness, test Toughness DR12. On a crit, they are healed; on a success, they are cured but you get the disease; on a fail, nothing changes; on a fumble, both of you are ill.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2576afd4-367b-4040-8b6c-5b75b2c2210f"}
{"name":"Peg Leg of Pozeid'nne","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> After losing your leg to the sea, a half-fish-half-man took pity and proffered this substitute of carved whale's bone. Its hollowed out base fills with concentrated brine overnight. Pouring the eroding liquid on a solid surface will make a hole - five feet wide and just as deep - within minutes. Don't drink it</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"25e8990e-d52a-4e9d-82d5-d05b6a250955"}
{"name":"Kything","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A wordless, mind to mind communication in which one person, almost becomes another, seeing through their eyes and feeling through their senses. Once linked, the two people intuitively know the meaning of what the other is telling them. Requires consent or a second Presence DR14 to force the Kything. Lose d2 HP every round you continue to stay connected.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2675877e-a855-4614-a45e-aa9e6b53c4b2"}
{"name":"BLOOD TELLS","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A flagellant, you regularly beat yourself to awaken your lost god. If you inflict d3 HP of damage to yourself prior to combat, you gain +2 to a number of rolls equal to the HP lost.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2746e955-2ab5-46d0-a4ba-5a153193be16"}
{"name":"MURDER-PLAGUED RAT","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Tiny= Agility tests, including defence, are DR8. Your bite (d4) carries disease, victims test DR14 Presence or attack their closest ally, until either is dead.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2793765a-87f1-4877-a1fb-ab1be777c56a"}
{"name":"Wizard Teeth","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Four weird teeth rattle within a blackened pouch. Before battle roll a d6 for each one. For every 6 one of your attacks deals maximum damage.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"27b79395-0beb-4e95-8a4c-4d84aee7d228"}
{"name":"TROLL CHILD","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> fists d8. Thick hide -2. Coward</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2c7ebf9a-cdac-4943-a689-fe7ce37da66c"}
{"name":"BEAR FROM BERGEN CHRYPT","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Hulking and massive= tests for Strength and Toughness, as well as attacks, are DR10. Defence is DR14. Thick hide, -d4 incoming damage. Your claws and bite deal d8 damage.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2e2be53c-21e3-46f6-8b35-b60ec89fb580"}
{"name":"Atonement Of The Heathen","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You can possess a target. Test Presence DR12 to succeed. Its body becomes paralyzed, but you can also control it with a result of 16+. Meanwhile, your own body will stay still and vulnerable, and if injured the bond will break. If the target is hurt, test Presence again to maintain the possession. Once inside their mind you can search for a specific memory. GM rolls a d6, on 1-2 the memory is distorted.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"2f84bd25-cd77-4bba-9b49-929ea0152a25"}
{"name":"Dark stigmata","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Open wounds from a past torture. You can touch the flesh of a foe with your palms to cause d6 damage. It cannot be healed, as it doesn't wound their body, but their soul.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"34613fca-94ae-4971-8f65-38fd1bb64450"}
{"name":"BLOODY LORIS","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> your eyes distract any human near giving you a +2 on attack/defence for 3 turns.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"352402d1-3787-4514-947b-e5b3ed0e1553"}
{"name":"Shepherd The Departed","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You can bring forth the spirits of the dead and speak with them. Test Presence DR12 to convince them to fight by your side. They'll never go far from where their body is resting. Their HP as a spirit is 1/3 of their normal HP.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"3650ed6d-6697-4e75-9e42-b0bf0fea3fcf"}
{"name":"Excretal Stealth","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You have an astounding, almost preternatural ability to hide in muck, debris and filth. When hidden in these conditions a DR16 Presence test is required to notice you.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"3e6f0123-7cd8-4325-b8d6-c7dded9ff2f8"}
{"name":"Saltstone Eye","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A scavenger pelican took your eye one night, but left something in its place. Your crusty socket itches constantly, but stings when danger is about to strike. Defence is DR10 and crits on a natural 19 as well as 20.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"40fbf973-df86-44a8-b330-a6b3ecbbaf44"}
{"name":"Soaking Cutlass","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Attacks and defends against DR10. Damage is d6 and on a 6, a wave of seawater erupts from the blade. Creatures in front of you must test Strength against DR12 or be knocked off their feet, taking d4 damage.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"44bd6ac2-d951-405b-81bb-fbc4fefd2e1e"}
{"name":"GODSHIELD CHELONIAN","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> This turtle can hide in its iron-like shell to become impervious to all damage. Doing so takes 5 minutes (during which the turtle can do nothing else). Emerging again takes 15 minutes. It is immobile and cannot act while hiding.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"4bf84999-17a1-43ed-91c4-029fb544736c"}
{"name":"FEARWIG","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A wound made by this pincer-assed insect will fill it's victim with primal fear. Bite/forceps d4 + Test Presence DR10 or flee/cower in fear for d10 rounds.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"4dc5f686-0ec1-4249-a72d-b820c90bd6e3"}
{"name":"GUTPIPES OF DESTINY","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> This amalgamation of sown, hairygutsacks feature extruding bone pipes for you to blow on. When doing so, listeners of your choosing are filled with unearthly hunger, as if they hadn't eaten for a week.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"5b96f140-1abe-403b-9cef-aad893a295d2"}
{"name":"EYES OF HOLY FIRE","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Your pupils burn with the soul of your lord. Once per combat you may make an attack (DR10), as fire spurts from your eyes, d6 damage. You are left blinded for the rest of the fight.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"606c9d6d-4d66-4378-b31b-033ce0c2b01e"}
{"name":"Bard of the Undying","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You learnt your melodies in the Otherworld. The music of your Harp gives +D4 on reaction rolls.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"624e7d78-cdb6-4c0a-af06-0b2455a2d716"}
{"name":"RUIN BASILISK","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> In the shape of this single-headed sacred beast you can fool the simple into devotion and worship (+5 to reaction checks) but scholars and priests will likely see through the fa'ade (-5 to reaction checks).</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"63899da3-50aa-4c02-a124-efeea45f2b49"}
{"name":"Stolen Mitre","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> While wearing this holy hat the priest's vile body fades, becoming hard to hit in combat (Defence DR10). If pulled over the ears outside of battle the priest becomes nearly invisible, testing stealth against DR8.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"6781eae1-df82-45db-bc1e-180a218a3965"}
{"name":"BLEATING DEVIL-RAM","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You can Ram for d8. On a 1-2 form a d6 the creature is toppled over and cant attack for a turn. Thick Black Fleece -d4 Hell's Bells, You have a Cursed bell around your neck and it rings with dread. Once a round you can make a creature test for Morale.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"68fab3e1-b3ff-4554-8bd5-0a81d12d9ee3"}
{"name":"'Poltroon' the Court Jester","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> While practically useless, personally irritating and an emotional drain, Poltroon's capering actually makes enemies lose their focus in combat. For the first two rounds you and your allies get +2 on attack/defence.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"6cfce87e-119f-4401-bc7c-d9796eea5f66"}
{"name":"A Book of Boiling Blood","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You may open and read from this book once a day. Your enemy must make a DR12 test to prevent this. If they fail D2 Berserker-slayers (see page 60) appear from the depths of a forgotten dimension of blood. Roll a D6. On a 1-4 these creatures fight alongside you. On a 5-6 they turn on you, attempting to kill you and destroy the book. After the battle they return to their imprisonment.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"6f0bff1b-45e8-431a-8f33-275432b0ef44"}
{"name":"The Blasphemous Nechrubel Bible","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> So intensely blasphemous even the Priests themselves can only peruse it once per day. When read, roll a die. Even result= For the rest of the day PCs heal d4 HP after just five minutes of rest. Odd result= The priest is plagued by demonic hallucinations. The DM may invent d3 things that only the Priest can see and describe them to the player as if true.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"71a1f946-3ea2-4e91-8ecc-4c36c543b903"}
{"name":"REGULAR MOLE","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You can dig a 6 feet deep hole per turn, but you are blind in daylight.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"72053f58-4c68-4ec0-8b27-6ec2c4457fc3"}
{"name":"Crumpled Monster Mask","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Strikes primitive fear into lesser creatures like goblins, gnoums and children. While worn, they check Morale every round.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"74d389bc-524b-4415-a1fd-e487133e5323"}
{"name":"LUTE OF THE ACUTE BRUTE","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> When strummed, the sound of this axe- shaped (d8 damage) instrument makes the  Strength and Presence score of anyone hearing it swap scores for the next d6 days. Repeated listening has no effect.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"77d63117-2685-480b-b222-6099e9be311c"}
{"name":"DOOMSAYING MONKEY","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p>  Dextrous= Agility tests, including defence, are DR10. Light armor and weapons remain Usable. Your third eye allows you to read unclean scrolls at DR10.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"78a8b0a8-d25e-43da-9acf-b560095ffb7b"}
{"name":"Psychokinesis","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The ability to manipulate objects by the mind. Move or manipulate small or medium sized objects that are within your line of sight. Lose 1 HP every round you continue the action.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"7a832069-05c6-4c03-b5fa-f83ca3825522"}
{"name":"Coward's Jab","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> When attacking by surprise test Agility DR10. On a success you automatically hit once with a light one-handed weapon, dealing normal damage +3.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"7a882b6f-8d21-4cb2-8bfd-f6dc68b2236c"}
{"name":"MEMBRANOUS WINGS","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You can fly short distances, but cannot wear armor. Birds seem to dislike you.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"7b3e64e3-b52e-4824-a3b4-0a1cbc269a3b"}
{"name":"Master of Fate","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> What use are maps when the substance of causality itself is open to you? You know the right way with a DR8 Presence test.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"7cef86da-bd43-4f7d-a89f-3fbecedee24e"}
{"name":"666 (WRONG JESUS) CRUCIFIX","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The crucifix can be used in encounters with the undead as well as lesser trolls and goblins. Check morale (add or subtract the priest's Presence modifier) to see if the creatures bow and kindly remove themselves.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"80dde1ea-8e53-4422-b200-b833a64122b8"}
{"name":"Dodging Death","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You are so unpleasant, irrelevant, disgusting and vile even Death would rather avoid you if it can. On death, if there is even the slightest possibility that you survived, there is a 50% chance that you did. If successful, after 10 rounds you pop back up with d4 HP and an unlikely explanation of your escape.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"833c8661-ff3c-42e8-a331-c6bf8ef12684"}
{"name":"Initiate of the Invisible College","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Once per day you may summon D2 scrolls, whose power can be used only once. Roll a d4, on a 1-2 the scrolls are sacred, on a 3-4, unclean. If the scrolls are not used before sunrise they turn to ash.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"8510ccb9-bc38-492d-a66c-4295b3750348"}
{"name":"MY BODY, A V ESSEL","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Your god may be dead, but what is death to a god? Once a day you may allow the ghost of you god to enter your flesh and reveal a truth. Ask the GM one yes/no question that they must answer truthfully. The god then departs, leaving you weakened and frail.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"86b1ed4f-1b61-4e7e-89d7-fad7456cc4ac"}
{"name":"LIFE-AND-DEATH-LIZARD","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Regenerate d4 HP per round. Bite (d6) or spit acid (d4, 1 in 4 chance armor is lowered one tier). Scaly skin, -d2 incoming damage.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"87827d58-8bc4-4e4e-97ff-cf13d28b89e3"}
{"name":"UNCOMMON CLAY","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> You can draw nourishment from soil, but normal food makes you sick. You smell like mushrooms.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"887dc5f4-9e14-4f92-9323-488fc7add7b5"}
{"name":"The Shoe of Death's Horse","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> It looks normal but since finding it in an obscure crypt you are convinced this shoe came from the horse of Death himself. In your hands it hits with DR10, d4 damage. 1 in 6 chance the shoe smashes the skull, instantly killing small-to-medium sized creatures. The shoe returns to your hand like a boomerang.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"89a46770-9d74-443d-bef1-ab37fb958408"}
{"name":"SPINAL HUSK","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> When beating this drum made from a hellion's shell, roll 2d6</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"8c3e755f-e1b2-427f-b66a-028fbbc7e022"}
{"name":"Hawk as weapon","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Your crafty almost-intelligent hawk is loyal only to you. Even without shared language, you understand its cries as it keeps watch, scouts and swoops to attack foes. Attacks/ defence DR10 (claws/bite D4), HP 8.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"93ac39e2-2360-4434-bc27-aacc2c4a7dae"}
{"name":"SMELL OF DECAY","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Not only is your god dead, but their odour of decay pervades you. Tests to defend against attacks have a +2 bonus due to the gut-wrenching stench.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"94f6ef41-5b9b-4326-be8d-efcd5f043a93"}
{"name":"HELL HOUND","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A shuddering beast covered in hanging icicles. d6 (frost bite). Can unleash a cone of freezing breath</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"9ca2dfe7-4255-4fc8-bc57-472e0399584f"}
{"name":"Hamfund the Squire","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> This intensely cowardly servant acts only as guardian for the scabbard of the cursed sword Eurekia. Once per combat, if Ham can be found, Eurekia may be drawn. The sword does 2d6 damage, and for every swing of Eurekia roll a d6. On a 1 the squire is slain and Eurekia vanishes forever.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"9dd2265d-9b99-4e15-86af-919c9aa5b6be"}
{"name":"Stones taken from Thel-Emas' Lost Temple","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Cast the stones on the ground. Their pattern reveals if danger lurks in an adjacent room. The stones can lie. The priest tests Presence DR10 to see if they are true but after failing they cannot test again until the sun has set.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"a1e9e698-62e4-4e6a-95d7-e5031b5a6b1f"}
{"name":"The Brown Scimitar of Galgenbeck","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A stinking sword you pulled from a military shit-ditch. D6 damage. DR10 attack and defence while you wield it. 1 in 6 chance a wounded enemy is smitten with potent sepsis, dying in 10 minutes.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"a3410107-fb6c-46be-8c71-e267e0a97b0b"}
{"name":"Barbarister the Incredible Horse","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Barbarister is magical, intelligent, arrogant and vain. He can also talk. If you can persuade him to care, Barbarister occasionally adds +2 to Presence tests involving logic and intellect. The horse may be smarter than you and is quite aware of this.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"a6cf43b8-8993-43c4-824b-421a395048ea"}
{"name":"Escaping Fate","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Every time you use an omen there is a 50% chance it is not spent.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"aa87e165-9593-4dcf-8ab2-c6ff8fe57393"}
{"name":"ABYSSAL CHICKEN AKA COCKATRICE BEAK","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> d4 damage and Stone Peck Stone Peck= 1. On the first successful attack, DR to defend decreases by 2 2. On the second successful attack, DR to attack decreases by 2 3. On third successful hit, target turns to stone for d4 days</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"ac949346-c82e-43df-a703-0b4b85653081"}
{"name":"IN DEATH I L IV E","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> When you die, make a DR14 Presence test. If you pass, your god refuses you into the afterlife and you recover with 1HP. If you fail, your body is consumed in holy flames.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"b109c9e3-1926-45c8-9124-468ae7b09c66"}
{"name":"Horn of the Schleswig Lords!","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Once per day release a blare from this dented old trumpet and test Presence DR12. One creature may make their next non-combat test an automatic success.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"b214f7cd-e3f0-4530-b4e9-06f6b23fbf42"}
{"name":"SHOCK SHARK","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Can instantly teleport to a spot within 30 feet in a flash of sparking electricity. d8 (nasty bite). If your victim is wearing armor, they take an additional d4 damage from sparks that fly from your teeth (ignoring armor). Can't survive out of water for long.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"b3a1c704-c102-47d4-9178-e480d2dc260d"}
{"name":"GOBLIN-SNIFFING DOG","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Bite d4, mottled fur -d2 Keen Nose= You can Sniff out Goblins in an adjacent room to you. Alarming Bark</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"b72f57fd-78c2-4dc3-8b68-295d4c4d3302"}
{"name":"HERMIT CRAB","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Has extremely sharp pinchers (d6 damage). Suffocates if not in water for longer than 2 hours at a time.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"bb203274-bcfb-4c49-b0d9-bfd4685f8bf1"}
{"name":"Old Sig'rd's sling","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Sig'rd was the strongest man whose throat you ever gnawed. Woven from his long grey hair, this sling has never failed you. 2d4 damage, requires fist-sized rocks which, perhaps regrettably, are everywhere.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"bd359747-6d76-4596-8891-af5d4dc0e80b"}
{"name":"Energy Healing","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The ability to heal with one's own empathic, mental energy. With one whom you are touching either heal them for d6 HP or remove one disease, infection, poison or disorder from their body via an energetic incision that heals immediately (you cannot heal yourself). In place of 'catching your breath' you can choose to meditate and restore d6 HP.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"bdddf646-51c6-48de-8419-4ad0136d534d"}
{"name":"Psychometry","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> The ability to obtain information about a person or an object by touch. Ask the DM a question.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"bffd8163-bd34-43aa-8676-8129dd0f442a"}
{"name":"HURTY-GURDY","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Cranking this stringed thing of wood and gore emits a droning sound that hurts the ears of creatures that fail a Presence test against DR12. The first round played, it deals d2 damage, increasing to a d4 and beyond on subsequent rounds.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"c1ad8494-7feb-4d07-a07d-8d5153f2ec61"}
{"name":"INCOHERENT SOPHISTIC BABBLE","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Concentrate to babble an ungodly litany. So disconcerting is this chant that those who hear it must pass a DR10 Presence test or lose their next action.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"c526d1a2-3428-4db7-b24e-e4832951e57e"}
{"name":"Few-feathered parrot","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A mangy yet murderous parrot friend. Throw it at an enemy and the bird attacks against DR10, dealing d4 damage. On a 4, it continues its deadly trajectory, instantly making an attack against another enemy. Can and will repeat things it hears. HP d6+1</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"c7bb56c7-5be2-4f26-b6e3-e6e55e86dd78"}
{"name":"Sacred shepherd's crook","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Its head a hook of human bone inscribed with overlapping anti-prayers. This crook hooks through other worlds. Staff does 2d4 damage except to faithless humans.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"c8e7b652-5c78-4c5d-970b-238f672abe72"}
{"name":"MOUTH-TO-MOUTH-ORGAN","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Play this bony mouth harp to make a broken listener instantly recover d4 HP. They cannot speak until their HP is fully recovered.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"d15aeff5-645d-43ed-8bde-b590ad1db989"}
{"name":"FLAYED AND DRIPPING WOLF","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Ferocious, attacks are DR10. Your fangs (d6) crit on a natural 19 as well as a 20. On a crit, all enemies test Morale. Slick from blood, -d2 incoming damage.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"d28c4e13-0580-488b-86ef-2a1d1828e3b7"}
{"name":"Abominable Gob Lobber","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Your phlegm is viscous, lumpy, vile and ballistically accurate at short range. You can spit d2 times during a fight. Roll a DR8 Presence test for accuracy. Targets are blinded, retching and vomiting for d4 rounds. Anyone witnessing this 'friend and foe' must make a Toughness test to not also vomit. PCs test DR10 and enemies DR12.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"d497a0ae-147f-4ab7-a43b-2e5180db95e6"}
{"name":"MANA FROM SOMEWHERE","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Spend a use of your Powers to create food for d6 people. It is weirdly delicious, but unsettling.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"d93f2c4d-fc7f-4c20-a088-4fb64728760a"}
{"name":"TOO MANY EYES","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Just way too many. You cannot be attacked from surprise. You can spend a use of your Powers to leave an eye behind, and spy on a remote area. If anyone squishes the eye, you take d2 damage.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"db2b49e0-d49c-48f7-98fe-b266aa044602"}
{"name":"SACRED MAN-FACED STAG","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Enormous Horns d8 , Golden Fleece -d6 Holy Light= You emit a blinding light. Creatures cannot come near you unless they pass a Morale if they pass you become their sole target. They want that Fleece. Healing Light= Allies near you gain d2 hp on your turn.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"de7f7525-560b-47d7-a580-92d06d475f06"}
{"name":"List of Sins","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> A long and accurate document cross-referenced against reality to discover unseen evil-doers. Successful Presence DR10= A strange light surrounds evil creatures. The list's owner defends with +2 against any being discovered this way.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"e0c881f0-c956-4940-9861-42e78c45686b"}
{"name":"Sand-filled Boots","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> These boots allow you to walk on water as if it were a beach. As you move, you leave floating footsteps, lasting a round. Others may test Agility against DR10 to follow behind.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"e3411638-83bb-4f54-a356-a2efcb4c61aa"}
{"name":"Filthy Fingersmith","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Your snaky little digits get into pockets and pick locks with a DR8 Agility test. You also begin with lockpicks!</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"e646e90a-14a9-4f2f-b8bd-df309f4d0a88"}
{"name":"THE STARS WERE RIGHT","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Roll d4+2 for omens. Say something cryptic every time you use one.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"e7bdb48d-1b70-43b5-af43-6b4d2c25e953"}
{"name":"BONE SKULLED RAVEN","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Fast and flying, defence is DR10. Make two attacks per round with your claws (d4). Your bony scalp (d6) acts as a weapon and a shield= -1 damage and you may choose to ignore all damage from one attack. The skull will heal in d6 days.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"e8ea56d8-ec74-4e07-a660-90ee27bb0e4d"}
{"name":"Cult Following","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Your messianic aura attracts devotees to your person. D4 disciples follow and obey you. (2 HP, punch/club d4) If you are in danger they will put their bodies between you and any harm coming your way. If one dies, a new one will occupy their spot in a couple of days. The first time the Unholy Spawn gets better add another d4 disciples to your following.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"f73ea3c8-48fc-4599-bce2-1be2d0ec815c"}
{"name":"The Blade of your Ancestors","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> This magnificent and clearly magical talking sword is foppish, unreliable and quietly despises you. It taunts your failures and, if continually disappointed, develops a 1 in 6 chance to 'accidentally' attack you or your companions. Deals d6+1 damage. Attack/Defence DR is 10.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"f9653ac8-0204-46b2-b690-9ac31b1e607d"}
{"name":"The Snake-Skin Gift","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> An expensive sandalwood box bound in snakeskin. It contains a seemingly ordinary dagger, wrapped in silk. The dagger does d4 damage but on a 1 the target dies immediately of deadly poison weeping from the blade.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"f9e1bfc8-5461-43b3-9cdd-908895c37b1c"}
{"name":"SPIKY HEDGEHOG","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> d6 throwing spikes. 1 on 6 chances of piercing yourself with these.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"fde1fb6d-7b0a-49a6-ab27-1103508b1c99"}
{"name":"SLIPPERY SLUG","permission":{"default":0},"type":"feature","data":{"description":"<p> Not affected by piercing attacks or razor weapons. +2 on attack/defence for 2 turns. Can't hold anything.</p>"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/bestiary/default.png","_id":"ffbf2b7f-ecec-4487-adae-7777487db675"}
